    <ThingDef ParentName="RNBaseAKStyle">
    <defName>RNGun_AKMAR</defName>
    <label>AKM</label>
    <description>The AKM (Russian: модернизи́рованный Автома́т Кала́шникова, tr. modernizírovanny Avtomát Kaláshnikova, lit. Modernized Kalashnikov Automatic Rifle) is a 7.62mm assault rifle designed by Mikhail Kalashnikov. It is a common modernized variant of the AK-47 rifle developed in the 1940s.

Introduced into service with the Soviet Army in 1959, the AKM is the most ubiquitous variant of the entire AK series of firearms and it has found widespread use with most member states of the former Warsaw Pact and its African and Asian allies as well as being widely exported and produced in many other countries.

It was officially replaced in Soviet frontline service by the AK-74 in the late 1970s, but remains in use worldwide.</description>
